al People's Party|CSV]]\n|---- bgcolor=#DDEEFF\n|[[European Commissioner for Economic & Financial Affairs|Economic affairs]] and [[European Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs & Equal Opportunities|employment]]\n|[[Alois Pfeiffer]]<ref>Until 1 August 1987, when replaced by [[Peter Schmidhuber]]</ref><ref name=\"Community 1986\">Portfolio shared with [[Abel Matutes]] after Spain joined the Community (5 January 1986)</ref>\n|{{DEU}}\n|[[Christian Social Union in Bavaria|CSU]]\n|---- bgcolor=#FFE8E8\n|[[European Commissioner for Administrative Affairs, Audit and Anti-Fraud|Institutional reforms]], [[European Commissioner for Institutional Relations & Communication Strategy|information policy]], [[European Commissioner for Education, Training & Culture|culture and tourism]]\n|[[Carlo Ripa di Meana]]\n|{{ITA}}\n|[[Italian Socialist Party|PSI]]\n|---- bgcolor=#DDEEFF\n|[[European Commissioner for Economic & Financial Affairs|Economic affairs]] and [[European Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs & Equal Opportunities|employment]]\n|[[Peter Schmidhuber]]<ref name=\"Community 1986\"/><ref>From 22 September 1987, replacing [[Alois Pfeiffer]]</ref>\n|{{DEU}}\n|[[Christian Social Union in Bavaria|CSU]]\n|----- bgcolor=#DDEEFF\n|[[Commissioner for Competition|Competition]], [[European Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs & Equal Opportunities|social affairs]] and [[European Commissioner for Education, Training & Culture|education]] \n|[[Peter Sutherland]]<ref>Portfolio shared with [[Manuel Marin]] after Spain joined the Community (5 January 1986)</ref>\n|{{IRL}}\n|[[Fine Gael]]\n|-\n|[[European Commissioner for Inter-Institutional Relations and Administration|Relations with the European Parliament]], [[European Commissioner for Regional Policy|regional policy]] and [[European Commissioner for Consumer Protection|consumer protection]]\n|[[Grigoris Varfis]]\n|{{GRE}}\n|[[Panhellenic Socialist Movement|PASOK]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Second college===\nThis Commission served from 1989 to 1992.\n\n{| class=wikitable width=100%\n|-\n!width=40%|Portfolio\n!Name\n!State\n!Party\n|---- bgcolor=#FFE8E8\n|[[President of the European Commission|President]]\n|[[Jacques Delors]]\n|{{FRA}}\n|[[Socialist Party (France)|PS]]\n|---- bgcolor=#DDEEFF\n|[[Vice-President of the European Commission|Vice-President]]<br>[[European Commissioner for External Relations|External relations]] and [[European Commissioner for Trade|trade policy]]\n|[[Frans Andriessen]]\n|{{NLD}}\n||[[Christian Democratic Appeal|CDA]]\n|---- bgcolor=#FFFFDD\n|[[Vice-President of the European Commission|Vice-President]]<br>[[European Commissioner for Internal Market & Services|Internal market]] and [[European Commissioner for Enterprise & Industry|industrial affairs]]\n|[[Martin Bangemann]]\n|{{DEU}}\n|[[Freie Demokratische Partei|FDP]]\n|---- bgcolor=#DDEEFF\n|[[Vice-President of the European Commission|Vice-President]]<br>[[European Commissioner for Competition|Competition]] and [[European Commissioner for Financial Programming & the Budget|financial institutions]]\n|[[Leon Brittan|Sir Leon Brittan]]\n|{{UK}}\n|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n|---- bgcolor=#FFFFDD\n|[[Vice-President of the European Commission|Vice-President]]<br>[[European Commissioner for Economic & Financial Affairs|Economic & financial affairs]] and [[European Commissioner for Development & Humanitarian Aid|coordination of structural funds]]\n|[[Henning Christophersen]]\n|{{DNK}}\n|[[Venstre (Denmark)|Venstre]]\n|---- bgcolor=#FFE8E8\n|[[Vice-President of the European Commission|Vice-President]]<br>[[European Commissioner for Development & Humanitarian Aid|Cooperation, development]] and [[European Commissioner for Fisheries & Maritime Affairs|fisheries]]\n|[[Manuel Marin]]\n|{{ESP}}\n|[[Spanish Socialist Workers' Party|PSOE]]\n|---- bgcolor=#DDEEFF\n|[[Vice-President of the European Commission|Vice-President]]<br>[[European Commissioner for Science & Research|Science, research, development, telec